00:00:53.821 --> 00:00:56.957 align:middle line:84%
to first hear what is actually
lucid dreaming so we're all

00:00:56.957 --> 00:01:00.227 align:middle line:84%
on the same page, the
obvious question.

00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:01.962 align:middle line:84%
>> Charlie Morley: So a
lucid dream is a dream

00:01:01.962 --> 00:01:03.497 align:middle line:84%
where you know that
you're dreaming.

00:01:03.497 --> 00:01:05.633 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just a
really vivid dream.

00:01:05.633 --> 00:01:08.235 align:middle line:84%
It's not a dream that
you remember very well.

00:01:08.235 --> 00:01:10.004 align:middle line:84%
It's specifically
being in a dream

00:01:10.004 --> 00:01:11.939 align:middle line:90%
and you're, aha, I'm dreaming.

00:01:11.939 --> 00:01:14.208 align:middle line:84%
Now once you have that moment
you will often remember the

00:01:14.208 --> 00:01:16.410 align:middle line:84%
dream very well and the dream
will often be very vivid

00:01:16.410 --> 00:01:18.145 align:middle line:84%
but that's not what
makes it lucid.

00:01:18.145 --> 00:01:20.448 align:middle line:84%
The definition of a lucid
dream is a dream where you go,

00:01:20.448 --> 00:01:23.184 align:middle line:84%
ah I know I'm dreaming as
the dream is happening.

00:01:23.184 --> 00:01:25.319 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: So you
can ignite it too?

00:01:25.319 --> 00:01:29.023 align:middle line:84%
I mean you can want
to dream and you dream

00:01:29.023 --> 00:01:30.723 align:middle line:84%
and that's also called
a lucid dreaming.

00:01:30.723 --> 00:01:33.360 align:middle line:84%
You can do that basically
anytime, day or night?

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:34.462 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, yeah,
that's what I do.

00:01:34.462 --> 00:01:36.229 align:middle line:84%
Yes, so teach people
how to have that at work

00:01:36.229 --> 00:01:38.232 align:middle line:84%
because most people might
have had that occasionally,

00:01:38.232 --> 00:01:39.567 align:middle line:90%
a spontaneous, lucid dream

00:01:39.567 --> 00:01:41.202 align:middle line:84%
and I'm sure most people
watching must say, oh yeah,

00:01:41.202 --> 00:01:42.336 align:middle line:90%
I know that experience.

00:01:42.336 --> 00:01:43.604 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's happened
once or twice.

00:01:43.604 --> 00:01:46.340 align:middle line:84%
So what I teach is the
techniques to allow people to do

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:48.509 align:middle line:84%
it at will, so a certain
meditation technique,

00:01:48.509 --> 00:01:50.478 align:middle line:84%
self-hypnosis techniques
and a lot obviously

00:01:50.478 --> 00:01:51.846 align:middle line:90%
from Tibetan Buddhism.

00:01:51.846 --> 00:01:55.249 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yeah, how is that
approach different to other ones

00:01:55.249 --> 00:01:57.551 align:middle line:84%
because there's a lot of
people that teach that,

00:01:57.551 --> 00:01:59.253 align:middle line:84%
obviously you're
a young teacher.

00:01:59.253 --> 00:02:00.020 align:middle line:90%
How old are you?

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:01.155 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Ah, 30.

00:02:01.155 --> 00:02:03.157 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: 30, my
goodness, you look like 20.

00:02:03.157 --> 00:02:05.693 align:middle line:90%
Anyway that's awesome.

00:02:05.693 --> 00:02:08.162 align:middle line:84%
Tell me how is your
approach new?

00:02:08.162 --> 00:02:15.135 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Well, I combine the
practices of Tibetan Buddhism

00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:18.539 align:middle line:84%
but in a way that's totally
accessible for non-Buddhists.

00:02:18.539 --> 00:02:21.208 align:middle line:84%
So, there's seen to be two
major camps in lucid dreaming,

00:02:21.208 --> 00:02:25.045 align:middle line:84%
the Western psychological field
which teaches the technique

00:02:25.045 --> 00:02:26.981 align:middle line:84%
to become lucid and
then kind of say, oh,

00:02:26.981 --> 00:02:28.448 align:middle line:84%
when you're lucid then
you can fly about.

00:02:28.448 --> 00:02:29.984 align:middle line:90%
You can meet movie stars.

00:02:29.984 --> 00:02:32.253 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you can do a bit of
shadow integration stuff

00:02:32.253 --> 00:02:35.322 align:middle line:84%
but it's quite, kind
of base level stuff.

00:02:35.322 --> 00:02:36.757 align:middle line:84%
And then you've got the
Tibetan Buddhist stuff

00:02:36.757 --> 00:02:38.792 align:middle line:84%
which can sometimes
seem quite inaccessible.

00:02:38.792 --> 00:02:41.095 align:middle line:84%
It's about going to the lucid
dream state, transforming

00:02:41.095 --> 00:02:43.063 align:middle line:84%
yourself into this deity and
this archetype of compassion --

00:02:43.063 --> 00:02:45.432 align:middle line:84%
That can seem quite far
out for a lot of people.

00:02:45.432 --> 00:02:47.234 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to deal with
something in the middle.

00:02:47.234 --> 00:02:50.070 align:middle line:84%
Some people who want to go
beyond the often-limited scope

00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:53.007 align:middle line:84%
of the Western psychological
view of lucid dreaming

00:02:53.007 --> 00:02:56.377 align:middle line:84%
but aren't quite ready
perhaps or aren't interested

00:02:56.377 --> 00:02:58.946 align:middle line:84%
in committing to the full-on
Tibetan dream yoga practices

00:02:58.946 --> 00:03:00.014 align:middle line:90%
but somewhere in the middle,

00:03:00.014 --> 00:03:01.749 align:middle line:84%
to make lucid dreaming
a spiritual path,

00:03:01.749 --> 00:03:03.150 align:middle line:84%
whether you're a
Buddhist, non-Buddhist

00:03:03.150 --> 00:03:04.552 align:middle line:90%
or anything in between.

00:03:04.552 --> 00:03:07.288 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yeah, it's even, what
do you mean by spiritual path?

00:03:07.288 --> 00:03:08.923 align:middle line:84%
Because it seems like
there's also some growth,

00:03:08.923 --> 00:03:13.193 align:middle line:84%
some real personal, you know,
growth and spiritual expansion

00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:15.663 align:middle line:84%
and all of that within because
you can change your life

00:03:15.663 --> 00:03:16.664 align:middle line:90%
through lucid dreaming.

00:03:16.664 --> 00:03:17.865 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're saying?

00:03:17.865 --> 00:03:19.233 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Yeah, absolutely,

00:03:19.233 --> 00:03:21.235 align:middle line:84%
I mean once you're lucid you're
conscious in the unconscious

00:03:21.235 --> 00:03:23.037 align:middle line:84%
which is a state most
people will only enter

00:03:23.037 --> 00:03:26.774 align:middle line:84%
into in deep-level meditation
and of course in hypnosis.

00:03:26.774 --> 00:03:30.177 align:middle line:84%
So it's a nice metaphor to use
that the hypnotic trance state

00:03:30.177 --> 00:03:32.580 align:middle line:84%
where the hypnotherapist
will guide an element

00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:34.748 align:middle line:84%
of your conscious mind
into the subconscious

00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:36.884 align:middle line:84%
and plant a suggestion
of healing intent.

00:03:36.884 --> 00:03:39.420 align:middle line:84%
Now in a lucid dream you're
doing the same thing but you're

00:03:39.420 --> 00:03:41.055 align:middle line:84%
in the depths of
the unconscious.

00:03:41.055 --> 00:03:43.023 align:middle line:84%
I mean you can't get more
unconscious than a sleep.

00:03:43.023 --> 00:03:45.259 align:middle line:84%
So if you plant a
suggestion of healing intent

00:03:45.259 --> 00:03:48.862 align:middle line:84%
in a lucid dream it can work
with often far greater efficacy

00:03:48.862 --> 00:03:51.732 align:middle line:84%
than if a hypnotherapist
implanted the suggestion.

00:03:51.732 --> 00:03:53.000 align:middle line:90%
Now in no way am I saying

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:54.735 align:middle line:84%
that makes lucid dreaming
better than hypnotherapy.

00:03:54.735 --> 00:03:56.870 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've had many years
training in self-hypnosis

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:58.072 align:middle line:90%
with a wonderful teacher

00:03:58.072 --> 00:04:00.708 align:middle line:84%
and actually hypnosis
is more accessible.

00:04:00.708 --> 00:04:02.943 align:middle line:84%
You know, right now we could go
into hypnotic trance within 20

00:04:02.943 --> 00:04:05.179 align:middle line:84%
or 30 minutes, to have
a lucid dream you've got

00:04:05.179 --> 00:04:06.513 align:middle line:84%
to be tired enough
to go to sleep.

00:04:06.513 --> 00:04:08.248 align:middle line:84%
Then you've got to go
through the deep-sleep stages.

00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:09.183 align:middle line:84%
Then you've got to
enter the dream.

00:04:09.183 --> 00:04:10.484 align:middle line:84%
You've got to know
the practices.

00:04:10.484 --> 00:04:12.720 align:middle line:84%
You've got to do this, that,
so it's not as accessible

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:15.155 align:middle line:84%
as hypnosis but once
you're in there,

00:04:15.155 --> 00:04:17.157 align:middle line:84%
because you're planting
the seed of the suggestion

00:04:17.157 --> 00:04:20.260 align:middle line:84%
so deep it works
very, very powerfully.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.495 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've had
somebody just,

00:04:21.495 --> 00:04:25.866 align:middle line:84%
coming up to his fifth
month now, of no cigarettes

00:04:25.866 --> 00:04:27.001 align:middle line:90%
after six years smoking.

00:04:27.001 --> 00:04:28.669 align:middle line:90%
He had one lucid dream and in

00:04:28.669 --> 00:04:30.337 align:middle line:84%
that lucid dream he
planted the suggestion.

00:04:30.337 --> 00:04:32.306 align:middle line:84%
He no longer was
addicted to cigarettes

00:04:32.306 --> 00:04:34.308 align:middle line:84%
and that the addiction
no longer served him

00:04:34.308 --> 00:04:35.409 align:middle line:90%
and he lived a healthy,

00:04:35.409 --> 00:04:37.511 align:middle line:84%
beneficial lifestyle,
free of cigarettes.

00:04:37.511 --> 00:04:39.747 align:middle line:90%
He hasn't smoked since that day.

00:04:39.747 --> 00:04:41.482 align:middle line:84%
You know, I bring that
guy out to workshops

00:04:41.482 --> 00:04:42.683 align:middle line:90%
to kind of tell his story.

00:04:42.683 --> 00:04:43.917 align:middle line:90%
People don't believe me.

00:04:43.917 --> 00:04:45.719 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's so, so powerful.

00:04:45.719 --> 00:04:49.089 align:middle line:84%
If you can have that lucid dream
you can make lasting changes

00:04:49.089 --> 00:04:52.026 align:middle line:84%
and direct interventions
within your own psychology.

00:04:52.026 --> 00:04:55.329 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yes, did you go
into the work with scientists

00:04:55.329 --> 00:04:57.464 align:middle line:84%
or had some kind
of understanding

00:04:57.464 --> 00:05:01.769 align:middle line:84%
of really how all this works
on a more like tangible basis?

00:05:01.769 --> 00:05:03.671 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, I mean, that's
what the book is full of.

00:05:03.671 --> 00:05:06.440 align:middle line:84%
The book looks at everything
from three major perspectives,

00:05:06.440 --> 00:05:09.743 align:middle line:84%
Western neuroscience,
psychology and Tibetan Buddhism.

00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:12.079 align:middle line:84%
So we even looked at the lucid
dream state from the point

00:05:12.079 --> 00:05:15.049 align:middle line:84%
of view of neuroscience and
those two other perspectives.

00:05:15.049 --> 00:05:16.316 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot
of science on it.

00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:17.918 align:middle line:84%
I mean this is why lucid
dreaming is becoming more

00:05:17.918 --> 00:05:19.853 align:middle line:84%
popular nowadays
because we have now the

00:05:19.853 --> 00:05:21.188 align:middle line:90%
science to back it up.

00:05:21.188 --> 00:05:22.523 align:middle line:84%
I mean it's first
scientifically proved

00:05:22.523 --> 00:05:24.725 align:middle line:84%
by Keith Hearne in
the early 70s.

00:05:24.725 --> 00:05:27.094 align:middle line:84%
But, just about two or three
years ago the Max-Planck

00:05:27.094 --> 00:05:29.663 align:middle line:84%
Institute and Heidelberg
University in Germany,

00:05:29.663 --> 00:05:32.800 align:middle line:84%
they started doing functional
magnetic resonance imaging scans

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:35.035 align:middle line:84%
on lucid dreamers so you could
actually see the moment they

00:05:35.035 --> 00:05:36.103 align:middle line:90%
became lucid.

00:05:36.103 --> 00:05:37.337 align:middle line:84%
So now we know we're
beyond anecdote.

00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:38.906 align:middle line:90%
It absolutely exists.

00:05:38.906 --> 00:05:41.842 align:middle line:84%
We know that it's the right
dorsolateral prefrontal cortex

00:05:41.842 --> 00:05:44.411 align:middle line:84%
that activates within the
dream state thus triggering

00:05:44.411 --> 00:05:45.778 align:middle line:90%
self-reflective awareness.

00:05:45.778 --> 00:05:47.314 align:middle line:90%
So there's no ifs, no buts.

00:05:47.314 --> 00:05:48.349 align:middle line:90%
It's now. It's real.

00:05:48.349 --> 00:05:49.750 align:middle line:90%
It's science.

00:05:49.750 --> 00:05:52.319 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: How does it look then
compared to the meditative state

00:05:52.319 --> 00:05:54.755 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the
brain at that stage?

00:05:54.755 --> 00:05:56.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Very similar,
if you look at somebody

00:05:56.190 --> 00:05:59.126 align:middle line:84%
in a lucid dream state they're
in a state of meditation.

00:05:59.126 --> 00:06:01.595 align:middle line:84%
In fact some of the highest
frequency brainwaves ever

00:06:01.595 --> 00:06:05.532 align:middle line:84%
recorded were in the brain of a
lucid dreaming subject so very,

00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:08.135 align:middle line:84%
very high frequency
and every moment spent

00:06:08.135 --> 00:06:10.804 align:middle line:84%
in the lucid dream is a moment
of mindful meditation.

00:06:10.804 --> 00:06:12.706 align:middle line:84%
You know if for one
minute you forget you're

00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:15.275 align:middle line:84%
in a lucid dream you're
going to slip out, you know,

00:06:15.275 --> 00:06:16.576 align:middle line:90%
you're going to wake up.

00:06:16.576 --> 00:06:18.512 align:middle line:84%
So there is this constant
awareness of the fact you're

00:06:18.512 --> 00:06:20.247 align:middle line:90%
in a dream as you're dreaming.

00:06:20.247 --> 00:06:22.783 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: How is it
different than the Dream Yoga

00:06:22.783 --> 00:06:24.518 align:middle line:84%
that you heard of
because I know you started

00:06:24.518 --> 00:06:25.819 align:middle line:84%
and you could maybe
tell us a little bit

00:06:25.819 --> 00:06:29.523 align:middle line:84%
about your story earlier
on at 12, 16 you had kind

00:06:29.523 --> 00:06:32.693 align:middle line:84%
of those moments where you
started just naturally,

00:06:32.693 --> 00:06:36.730 align:middle line:84%
just lucid dreaming but
it was more for fun, huh?

00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:39.600 align:middle line:84%
And at some point you
encountered Buddhism?

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:42.369 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yes, so let's look at
both aspects of that question.

00:06:42.369 --> 00:06:44.037 align:middle line:84%
The first one is
about Dream Yoga.

00:06:44.037 --> 00:06:46.507 align:middle line:84%
So Dream Yoga is the name
given to a collection

00:06:46.507 --> 00:06:48.509 align:middle line:84%
of practices found
within Tibetan Buddhism

00:06:48.509 --> 00:06:50.677 align:middle line:84%
that have lucid dream
training at their core.

00:06:50.677 --> 00:06:53.514 align:middle line:84%
But Dream Yoga contains
both out-of-body experiences

00:06:53.514 --> 00:06:55.482 align:middle line:84%
as we call it in the
West, conscious sleeping

00:06:55.482 --> 00:06:57.151 align:middle line:90%
and lucid dream practice.

00:06:57.151 --> 00:07:00.387 align:middle line:84%
Dream Yoga is traditionally
found within certain aspects,

00:07:00.387 --> 00:07:02.823 align:middle line:84%
certain lineages of
Tibetan Buddhism.

00:07:02.823 --> 00:07:05.959 align:middle line:84%
When I first got into lucid
dream training at the age

00:07:05.959 --> 00:07:10.030 align:middle line:84%
of kind of 16, after being aware
of it at 12, but then going back

00:07:10.030 --> 00:07:12.466 align:middle line:84%
to being a 12-year-old and
when about 16 when I got

00:07:12.466 --> 00:07:14.268 align:middle line:84%
into it I wasn't
into any of that.

00:07:14.268 --> 00:07:16.470 align:middle line:84%
I was into about having
sex in the lucid dream

00:07:16.470 --> 00:07:18.939 align:middle line:84%
because a lucid dream is
like super, super realistic.

00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:21.141 align:middle line:84%
You know, you're in there
and it feels as real as this.

00:07:21.141 --> 00:07:22.476 align:middle line:90%
You can feel your heart beating.

00:07:22.476 --> 00:07:24.678 align:middle line:90%
You feel the hair on your arms.

00:07:24.678 --> 00:07:26.079 align:middle line:90%
It's so, so real.

00:07:26.079 --> 00:07:28.515 align:middle line:84%
So when you have that as
a 16-year-old you want

00:07:28.515 --> 00:07:31.919 align:middle line:84%
to like do what you're into at
16 which for me was just sex.

00:07:31.919 --> 00:07:33.620 align:middle line:84%
So I'd just go into the lucid
dream state and call

00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:35.689 align:middle line:84%
out for like all
these girls to appear

00:07:35.689 --> 00:07:38.058 align:middle line:84%
and just spend my whole
lucid dreams having sex.

00:07:38.058 --> 00:07:40.594 align:middle line:84%
And luckily a few years
later I got into Buddhism

00:07:40.594 --> 00:07:42.528 align:middle line:84%
and somebody mentioned
this term, Dream Yoga,

00:07:42.528 --> 00:07:43.931 align:middle line:84%
and I was like, what's
Dream Yoga?

00:07:43.931 --> 00:07:45.332 align:middle line:90%
And they explained it.

00:07:45.332 --> 00:07:48.402 align:middle line:84%
And I said, oh, well I can do
lucid dream and the monk said,

00:07:48.402 --> 00:07:50.070 align:middle line:84%
you know, what do you
do in your lucid dreams?

00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:51.905 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, oh, you know.

00:07:51.905 --> 00:07:53.207 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to tell him.

00:07:53.207 --> 00:07:55.242 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well you know,
what do you do as a monk?

00:07:55.242 --> 00:07:56.443 align:middle line:90%
What are you supposed to do?

00:07:56.443 --> 00:07:58.312 align:middle line:84%
And we said, oh we use it
for spiritual practice.

00:07:58.312 --> 00:08:01.849 align:middle line:84%
We use it for exploring the
very essence of reality.

00:08:01.849 --> 00:08:04.418 align:middle line:84%
We use it for training and
exploration of emptiness.

00:08:04.418 --> 00:08:05.919 align:middle line:90%
And I was thinking, wow.

00:08:05.919 --> 00:08:07.020 align:middle line:90%
You know, I had no idea.

00:08:07.020 --> 00:08:08.388 align:middle line:84%
I thought this stuff
was just for kind of sex

00:08:08.388 --> 00:08:10.424 align:middle line:84%
and skateboarding which is what
I was using it for up till then.

00:08:10.424 --> 00:08:12.960 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly this door
opened and I realized it's

00:08:12.960 --> 00:08:15.629 align:middle line:84%
like I was holding a baby
and going, what does it do?

00:08:15.629 --> 00:08:16.997 align:middle line:90%
What does it do?

00:08:16.997 --> 00:08:18.699 align:middle line:84%
You know, a baby doesn't really
do anything but you nurture

00:08:18.699 --> 00:08:20.868 align:middle line:84%
that baby and you might
have the next Gandhi

00:08:20.868 --> 00:08:22.769 align:middle line:84%
or next Nelson Mandela
on your hands,

00:08:22.769 --> 00:08:24.705 align:middle line:90%
so too with lucid dreaming.

00:08:24.705 --> 00:08:26.940 align:middle line:84%
It's a potential
which we can waste

00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:29.810 align:middle line:84%
on just meeting movie stars
and having sex with elements

00:08:29.810 --> 00:08:33.046 align:middle line:84%
of our self but we can
also go one step further

00:08:33.046 --> 00:08:36.516 align:middle line:84%
into deep self-development
and spiritual realization

00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:37.918 align:middle line:90%
in fact while we sleep.

00:08:37.918 --> 00:08:39.286 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Yeah, were you able

00:08:39.286 --> 00:08:42.556 align:middle line:84%
to also lucid dream once you
start meditating because I guess

00:08:42.556 --> 00:08:46.159 align:middle line:84%
when you start looking at
Tibetan and getting closer

00:08:46.159 --> 00:08:51.398 align:middle line:84%
to the, to this Lama, then maybe
you have started

00:08:51.398 --> 00:08:52.833 align:middle line:90%
changing your practice?

00:08:52.833 --> 00:08:54.034 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Yeah, I mean one

00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:55.569 align:middle line:84%
of the original lucid
dream induction techniques

00:08:55.569 --> 00:08:56.904 align:middle line:90%
is meditation.

00:08:56.904 --> 00:08:59.172 align:middle line:84%
You do enough meditation,
you're going to start to have,

00:08:59.172 --> 00:09:02.476 align:middle line:84%
kind of clearer dreams and
often spontaneous lucid dreams,

00:09:02.476 --> 00:09:05.045 align:middle line:84%
people who do long, extended
periods of meditation.

00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:07.614 align:middle line:84%
So that definitely fills up
the lucidity tank, as it were.

00:09:07.614 --> 00:09:10.183 align:middle line:84%
And also when I got
into it because I was

00:09:10.183 --> 00:09:12.753 align:middle line:84%
into lucid dreaming I was
looking at certain meditations

00:09:12.753 --> 00:09:15.689 align:middle line:84%
that were linked to the
Dream Yoga practices.

00:09:15.689 --> 00:09:17.124 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are
kind of inaccessible

00:09:17.124 --> 00:09:19.660 align:middle line:84%
and you're not really supposed
to do until you're on retreat

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:21.728 align:middle line:84%
and stuff but at a young
age I was finding a way

00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:24.698 align:middle line:84%
to find these techs and trying
them out and stuff like that.

00:09:24.698 --> 00:09:26.233 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, meditation is
most definitely linked

00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:27.568 align:middle line:90%
to the practice.

00:09:27.568 --> 00:09:30.637 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yeah, it must have
helped because on going back

00:09:30.637 --> 00:09:32.873 align:middle line:84%
to the brain now,
there's neuroplasticity

00:09:32.873 --> 00:09:34.207 align:middle line:90%
that happening, you becoming.

00:09:34.207 --> 00:09:37.511 align:middle line:84%
It's becoming easier and
easier I guess as people train.

00:09:37.511 --> 00:09:40.681 align:middle line:84%
They can get quicker into
that stage because it's quite.

00:09:40.681 --> 00:09:44.117 align:middle line:84%
It's quite something I mean
from the outside to think of it

00:09:44.117 --> 00:09:46.053 align:middle line:84%
for people that have never
done it, like me, you know.

00:09:46.053 --> 00:09:48.922 align:middle line:84%
We're like, wow, how
cool is this stuff?

00:09:48.922 --> 00:09:50.524 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Yeah, and it is cool

00:09:50.524 --> 00:09:53.493 align:middle line:84%
and the neuroplasticity thing
is one of the coolest aspects.

00:09:53.493 --> 00:09:55.829 align:middle line:84%
You know, in a non-lucid dream,
let's say you're dreaming

00:09:55.829 --> 00:09:58.632 align:middle line:84%
about cycling or something you
might wake up in the morning

00:09:58.632 --> 00:10:01.101 align:middle line:84%
and say, oh, I dreamt about
cycling, maybe I'll want

00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:02.903 align:middle line:90%
to go cycling a little bit more

00:10:02.903 --> 00:10:04.304 align:middle line:84%
but nothing's really
happened in the brain.

00:10:04.304 --> 00:10:05.872 align:middle line:90%
If you have a lucid dream

00:10:05.872 --> 00:10:09.443 align:middle line:84%
about going cycling the lucid
dream state is so realistic

00:10:09.443 --> 00:10:11.511 align:middle line:84%
that the brain thinks
you're cycling

00:10:11.511 --> 00:10:14.548 align:middle line:84%
so it starts sending
electrical impulses

00:10:14.548 --> 00:10:17.584 align:middle line:84%
and increased blood flow to the
muscles engaged with cycling.

00:10:17.584 --> 00:10:19.252 align:middle line:84%
So they've shown that
if you lucid dream

00:10:19.252 --> 00:10:22.522 align:middle line:84%
about riding a bike the next
day you're better at it.

00:10:22.522 --> 00:10:24.257 align:middle line:84%
So you can practice
in the lucid dream

00:10:24.257 --> 00:10:25.926 align:middle line:90%
and learn to become better.

00:10:25.926 --> 00:10:28.862 align:middle line:84%
If you do press-ups in the lucid
dream you can increase muscle

00:10:28.862 --> 00:10:30.397 align:middle line:90%
mass in the waking state.

00:10:30.397 --> 00:10:31.631 align:middle line:90%
I mean this is nuts.

00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.800 align:middle line:84%
You're leaving lasting
neuro-pathways

00:10:33.800 --> 00:10:36.603 align:middle line:84%
in the very fabric of the brain
based on what you choose to do

00:10:36.603 --> 00:10:37.971 align:middle line:90%
in the lucid dream state.

00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:39.973 align:middle line:84%
The Heidelberg University, I
mean they have a lot of studies

00:10:39.973 --> 00:10:43.510 align:middle line:84%
like 350 professional athletes
have been trained to lucid dream

00:10:43.510 --> 00:10:45.912 align:middle line:84%
because they see the
potential and this is so high

00:10:45.912 --> 00:10:47.447 align:middle line:84%
because if you can get
better at your sport

00:10:47.447 --> 00:10:50.417 align:middle line:84%
in your sleep you've got
like a third, you've got kind

00:10:50.417 --> 00:10:51.784 align:middle line:90%
of eight hours extra a night

00:10:51.784 --> 00:10:54.254 align:middle line:84%
where you can be training while
the competition is snoozing.

00:10:54.254 --> 00:10:56.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: How is it better or
more efficient I should say

00:10:56.890 --> 00:10:58.692 align:middle line:90%
than the visualization?

00:10:58.692 --> 00:11:01.728 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Well, interestingly
the controlled study

00:11:01.728 --> 00:11:03.964 align:middle line:84%
that we're using in this was
visualized training.

00:11:03.964 --> 00:11:06.400 align:middle line:84%
So right now I can visualize
I'm on a bike, right?

00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:07.801 align:middle line:84%
I'm really, really
visualizing I'm on a bike.

00:11:07.801 --> 00:11:10.003 align:middle line:84%
I feel the handlebars but I
know I'm not riding a bike

00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:13.073 align:middle line:84%
and I'm sitting with you whereas
in the lucid dream state it's

00:11:13.073 --> 00:11:16.676 align:middle line:84%
so realistic the brain thinks
you're actually cycling.

00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:17.978 align:middle line:90%
You know, lucid dreaming

00:11:17.978 --> 00:11:20.213 align:middle line:84%
about doing something isn't
just like visualizing it.

00:11:20.213 --> 00:11:21.515 align:middle line:90%
It isn't like imagining it.

00:11:21.515 --> 00:11:23.183 align:middle line:84%
It's like you're
actually doing it

00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:25.919 align:middle line:84%
because it's 100
percent visualization,

00:11:25.919 --> 00:11:29.556 align:middle line:84%
so complete in fact that the
brain mistakes it for reality.

00:11:29.556 --> 00:11:30.757 align:middle line:90%
So it thinks you're doing this

00:11:30.757 --> 00:11:32.559 align:middle line:84%
so if you engage
a physical action

00:11:32.559 --> 00:11:35.062 align:middle line:84%
in a lucid dream state the
motor cortex sends a

00:11:35.062 --> 00:11:37.030 align:middle line:84%
command saying, you
know, move your legs.

00:11:37.030 --> 00:11:38.899 align:middle line:84%
Luckily you're paralyzed
during dream and sleep

00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:40.067 align:middle line:90%
so your legs don't move.

00:11:40.067 --> 00:11:41.802 align:middle line:84%
The electrical impulses
still make it through

00:11:41.802 --> 00:11:43.737 align:middle line:90%
and leave that muscle memory.

00:11:43.737 --> 00:11:45.439 align:middle line:84%
Now we're talking
about, you know, cycling

00:11:45.439 --> 00:11:46.406 align:middle line:90%
and press-ups and stuff.

00:11:46.406 --> 00:11:47.741 align:middle line:84%
What the hell's the
point of that?

00:11:47.741 --> 00:11:49.943 align:middle line:84%
But imagine if we can practise
other things, our capacity

00:11:49.943 --> 00:11:53.413 align:middle line:84%
for compassion, kindness, being
the person we know we could be

00:11:53.413 --> 00:11:56.650 align:middle line:90%
but have, are too scared to be.

00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:59.052 align:middle line:84%
Working on our meditation
training in our sleep,

00:11:59.052 --> 00:12:01.288 align:middle line:84%
working on our spiritual
practice in our sleep,

00:12:01.288 --> 00:12:02.823 align:middle line:84%
you know there are far
better things to be doing

00:12:02.823 --> 00:12:05.425 align:middle line:84%
than just press-ups but
the physical manifestation

00:12:05.425 --> 00:12:09.296 align:middle line:84%
of it is the easiest kind
of example to get people to.

00:12:09.296 --> 00:12:12.165 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: You say that we
can work on our shadow?

00:12:12.165 --> 00:12:14.334 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah,
so the shadow is.

00:12:14.334 --> 00:12:16.236 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: How do you define
it and how can we do that?

00:12:16.236 --> 00:12:18.205 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, so the
shadow is a Jungian term,

00:12:18.205 --> 00:12:21.575 align:middle line:84%
well Jung kind of pioneered the
term, used to describe the parts

00:12:21.575 --> 00:12:25.178 align:middle line:84%
of the unconscious that we've
denied, disowned or rejected.

00:12:25.178 --> 00:12:28.982 align:middle line:84%
So the shadow is the dark
side of the human psyche.

00:12:28.982 --> 00:12:31.218 align:middle line:84%
But dark doesn't
necessarily mean bad.

00:12:31.218 --> 00:12:32.319 align:middle line:90%
You know, for a lot of people,

00:12:32.319 --> 00:12:34.287 align:middle line:84%
the shadow contains a
repressed sexuality,

00:12:34.287 --> 00:12:36.990 align:middle line:84%
their oppressed anger, their
oppressed capacity for wrath

00:12:36.990 --> 00:12:41.094 align:middle line:84%
and aggression and yet it
will also contain the elements

00:12:41.094 --> 00:12:45.332 align:middle line:84%
that you feel you're not worthy
to accept within yourself.

00:12:45.332 --> 00:12:47.200 align:middle line:84%
So let's say I'm a
little boy and I'm dancing

00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:49.803 align:middle line:84%
around the bedroom, seven
years old and my dad walks in

00:12:49.803 --> 00:12:50.837 align:middle line:90%
and says, oh, stop dancing.

00:12:50.837 --> 00:12:52.005 align:middle line:90%
You know, dancing is for girls.

00:12:52.005 --> 00:12:53.940 align:middle line:84%
I will then repress
my inner dancer

00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:55.942 align:middle line:90%
into the shadows of my mind.

00:12:55.942 --> 00:12:58.578 align:middle line:84%
So that will, so the shadow
will contain my inner dancer

00:12:58.578 --> 00:12:59.780 align:middle line:90%
archetype as well.

00:12:59.780 --> 00:13:01.381 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just kind of
bad things in the shadow.

00:13:01.381 --> 00:13:03.049 align:middle line:84%
But for a lot of people
it is the dark side

00:13:03.049 --> 00:13:04.217 align:middle line:90%
of the human psyche.

00:13:04.217 --> 00:13:05.585 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: When you come,
become a hip-hop dancer?

00:13:05.585 --> 00:13:07.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: You can't
become a hip-hop dancer.

00:13:07.120 --> 00:13:08.488 align:middle line:90%
You need to bring this out.

00:13:08.488 --> 00:13:11.791 align:middle line:84%
So in the lucid dream state
you can intentionally integrate

00:13:11.791 --> 00:13:12.959 align:middle line:90%
shadow aspects.

00:13:12.959 --> 00:13:14.461 align:middle line:84%
Now of course the shadow
is being integrated,

00:13:14.461 --> 00:13:15.996 align:middle line:90%
non-lucid dreaming as well

00:13:15.996 --> 00:13:19.766 align:middle line:84%
as through Jungian
analytical psychology, therapy,

00:13:19.766 --> 00:13:21.134 align:middle line:90%
other forms of dream work.

00:13:21.134 --> 00:13:23.837 align:middle line:84%
But in the lucid dream state
you can do it very directly.

00:13:23.837 --> 00:13:26.940 align:middle line:84%
Because you can actually meet a
personified form of your shadow

00:13:26.940 --> 00:13:28.642 align:middle line:84%
which is rare and
almost exclusive

00:13:28.642 --> 00:13:31.511 align:middle line:84%
to the lucid dream state, to
be able to actually converse

00:13:31.511 --> 00:13:34.447 align:middle line:84%
with your shadow not as
a concept but actually

00:13:34.447 --> 00:13:36.516 align:middle line:84%
as a seemingly physicalized
being.

00:13:36.516 --> 00:13:39.786 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Tell us about
your experience with a demon.

00:13:39.786 --> 00:13:41.288 align:middle line:90%
Facing a demon, my God.

00:13:41.288 --> 00:13:45.358 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, so when I
first started lucid dreaming,

00:13:45.358 --> 00:13:48.828 align:middle line:84%
teaching lucid dreaming I
had a lot, kind of repression

00:13:48.828 --> 00:13:51.498 align:middle line:84%
around the things that I
should or shouldn't be doing

00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:52.933 align:middle line:90%
in the lucid dream state.

00:13:52.933 --> 00:13:56.136 align:middle line:84%
I kind of had this idea that
my Buddhist teacher was going

00:13:56.136 --> 00:13:58.738 align:middle line:84%
to look at my dream diary and if
I was having any lucid dreams

00:13:58.738 --> 00:14:02.509 align:middle line:84%
about kind of sex or violence
that I'd get like chucked out

00:14:02.509 --> 00:14:04.177 align:middle line:84%
and I wouldn't be
allowed to teach anymore.

00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:07.013 align:middle line:84%
So I started to become really
repressive with my dreaming

00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:08.615 align:middle line:84%
and if I was having
a lucid dream,

00:14:08.615 --> 00:14:10.817 align:middle line:84%
like a sexy girl turned up, so
I was going no, push it away,

00:14:10.817 --> 00:14:12.719 align:middle line:84%
don't want any of that or
there was some violence.

00:14:12.719 --> 00:14:13.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I don't want any of that.

00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:15.388 align:middle line:84%
I just want to sit and
meditate in a lucid dream.

00:14:15.388 --> 00:14:16.723 align:middle line:90%
And when I was doing this I saw

00:14:16.723 --> 00:14:19.192 align:middle line:84%
that these shadow aspects
became more and more powerful

00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:21.795 align:middle line:84%
and I started getting these
kinds of shadow attacks,

00:14:21.795 --> 00:14:23.163 align:middle line:84%
basically like nightmares.
You're in

00:14:23.163 --> 00:14:25.232 align:middle line:84%
a lucid dream and these big
kind of demonic figures appear

00:14:25.232 --> 00:14:27.100 align:middle line:90%
and I started fighting them.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.201 align:middle line:84%
I thought that's the
best thing to do.

00:14:28.201 --> 00:14:29.669 align:middle line:90%
I should fight these things.

00:14:29.669 --> 00:14:33.073 align:middle line:84%
And I asked my teacher
and he was like, no,

00:14:33.073 --> 00:14:34.374 align:middle line:90%
this could be a shadow element.

00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:36.076 align:middle line:84%
You shouldn't fight it,
you should embrace it.

00:14:36.076 --> 00:14:41.147 align:middle line:84%
So these demons came up and
the kind of famous one, well,

00:14:41.147 --> 00:14:44.751 align:middle line:84%
the one I talk about a lot
is when the demon appeared

00:14:44.751 --> 00:14:48.121 align:middle line:84%
in this kind of three-headed
figure and I hugged it rather

00:14:48.121 --> 00:14:49.189 align:middle line:90%
than running away from it.

00:14:49.189 --> 00:14:50.857 align:middle line:84%
And when I hugged it,
it turned into me.

00:14:50.857 --> 00:14:56.062 align:middle line:84%
And I was like hugging myself
and this version of myself kind

00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:58.665 align:middle line:84%
of looked at me and just
went, and then I woke up.

00:14:58.665 --> 00:15:00.533 align:middle line:84%
And I never had any
more of those nightmares

00:15:00.533 --> 00:15:02.035 align:middle line:90%
or shadow attacks again.

00:15:02.035 --> 00:15:03.970 align:middle line:84%
Now I don't know whether
that was, you know,

00:15:03.970 --> 00:15:06.906 align:middle line:84%
my directly hugging my shadow
but I talked to my teacher

00:15:06.906 --> 00:15:08.241 align:middle line:90%
and he seemed to think it was.

00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:10.410 align:middle line:84%
But then he said, you
know, you're crazy,

00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.245 align:middle line:84%
I didn't mean literally
hug the thing.

00:15:12.245 --> 00:15:13.079 align:middle line:90%
And I said, what do you mean?

00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:14.281 align:middle line:90%
You said, embrace the shadow.

00:15:14.281 --> 00:15:16.650 align:middle line:84%
And he said, yeah, embrace
the shadow means like,

00:15:16.650 --> 00:15:19.152 align:middle line:84%
that you know, talk to it,
engage it, the seeing of the,

00:15:19.152 --> 00:15:20.754 align:middle line:90%
don't literally hug it.

00:15:20.754 --> 00:15:21.988 align:middle line:90%
But since then he said, no,

00:15:21.988 --> 00:15:24.658 align:middle line:84%
do hug it because the
lucid dream state is unique

00:15:24.658 --> 00:15:27.327 align:middle line:84%
in that it allows you
to interact physically

00:15:27.327 --> 00:15:30.830 align:middle line:84%
with projections
of your own psyche.

00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:33.466 align:middle line:84%
You know, in the lucid dream
you can meet your inner child

00:15:33.466 --> 00:15:35.201 align:middle line:84%
which will often
appear as someone

00:15:35.201 --> 00:15:36.870 align:middle line:84%
who looked a bit
like you as a kid.

00:15:36.870 --> 00:15:39.773 align:middle line:84%
You know, you can
meet your higher self.

00:15:39.773 --> 00:15:42.909 align:middle line:84%
You can meet the whore, the
mother, the lovers, the fool,

00:15:42.909 --> 00:15:46.546 align:middle line:84%
all of the deck of the tarot,
all of the tarot deck in you.

00:15:46.546 --> 00:15:48.682 align:middle line:84%
You know, these archetypes
reside within your psyche

00:15:48.682 --> 00:15:51.184 align:middle line:84%
and in the lucid dream state
you can meet them tangibly

00:15:51.184 --> 00:15:52.686 align:middle line:90%
which is amazing.

00:15:52.686 --> 00:15:54.287 align:middle line:84%
You know this stuff
never gets old.

00:15:54.287 --> 00:15:57.157 align:middle line:84%
It's so fascinating and
it's so psychedelic.

00:15:57.157 --> 00:15:58.224 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Yeah.

00:15:58.224 --> 00:15:58.992 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: I mean
anyone who's into kind

00:15:58.992 --> 00:16:00.060 align:middle line:90%
of psychedelic experience,

00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:02.062 align:middle line:84%
you want a real psychedelic
experience,

00:16:02.062 --> 00:16:04.230 align:middle line:90%
walk around your own psyche.

00:16:04.230 --> 00:16:06.333 align:middle line:84%
In a lucid dream, you
know, you're aware

00:16:06.333 --> 00:16:07.233 align:middle line:90%
that everything is you.

00:16:07.233 --> 00:16:08.968 align:middle line:90%
You go, wow, this chair is me.

00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:10.804 align:middle line:84%
This Lilou is a feminine
projection

00:16:10.804 --> 00:16:12.539 align:middle line:90%
of my own psyche, wow.

00:16:12.539 --> 00:16:14.541 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly any boundaries
between us would break

00:16:14.541 --> 00:16:16.209 align:middle line:90%
down because I realize,

00:16:16.209 --> 00:16:18.845 align:middle line:84%
oh you're not separate
from me, you are me.

00:16:18.845 --> 00:16:20.547 align:middle line:84%
Now imagine if we could do
that in the waking state.

00:16:20.547 --> 00:16:21.948 align:middle line:84%
Imagine if we could
walk down the street

00:16:21.948 --> 00:16:24.351 align:middle line:84%
and just take a moment to think,
these people weren't separate

00:16:24.351 --> 00:16:27.620 align:middle line:84%
from us, they're
projections of our own dream,

00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:30.123 align:middle line:90%
sharing the dream with us.

00:16:30.123 --> 00:16:31.324 align:middle line:90%
Think what we could do.

00:16:31.324 --> 00:16:33.626 align:middle line:84%
It would be so much harder
to be unkind to someone

00:16:33.626 --> 00:16:35.261 align:middle line:84%
if you knew they
were part of you

00:16:35.261 --> 00:16:37.931 align:middle line:84%
and lucid dreaming allows you
to open up to that potential.

00:16:37.931 --> 00:16:41.067 align:middle line:84%
So in the waking state it
makes it easier to realize.

00:16:41.067 --> 00:16:44.003 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Can we
say life is a dream?

00:16:44.003 --> 00:16:45.271 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah,
we could say it.

00:16:45.271 --> 00:16:49.709 align:middle line:84%
I think it's probably an
overly simplistic thing to say

00:16:49.709 --> 00:16:54.147 align:middle line:84%
but I think life is far
more like a shared dream

00:16:54.147 --> 00:16:57.317 align:middle line:84%
than an inherently
existing reality

00:16:57.317 --> 00:16:58.717 align:middle line:90%
that we believe it to be.

00:16:58.717 --> 00:17:00.887 align:middle line:84%
You know, I don't think it's as
simple as, oh, it's all a dream

00:17:00.887 --> 00:17:03.990 align:middle line:84%
but it's definitely
dreamlike, definitely dreamlike.

00:17:03.990 --> 00:17:06.092 align:middle line:84%
And I think in the same ways,
if we can become lucid

00:17:06.092 --> 00:17:09.029 align:middle line:84%
in our dreams, we can
so co-create and start

00:17:09.029 --> 00:17:12.332 align:middle line:84%
to manifest the dream at will
within the confines of course

00:17:12.332 --> 00:17:14.000 align:middle line:90%
of the power of the unconscious.

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.970 align:middle line:84%
So, too, in this waking state
can we start to manifest,

00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:18.338 align:middle line:90%
can we start to wake up to life,

00:17:18.338 --> 00:17:22.542 align:middle line:84%
can we start to create the
dream that we want to be dreamt.

00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:24.244 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: We're going to
go into the practical side

00:17:24.244 --> 00:17:26.679 align:middle line:90%
and how we do that, but I hear,

00:17:26.679 --> 00:17:30.150 align:middle line:84%
what is your relationship
to alarm clock?

00:17:30.150 --> 00:17:32.118 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Pretty
good, definitely not.

00:17:32.118 --> 00:17:33.219 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Any others --

00:17:33.219 --> 00:17:35.255 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Like, oh
God, get away from me

00:17:35.255 --> 00:17:37.123 align:middle line:84%
but I do have a pretty
cool alarm clock you know.

00:17:37.123 --> 00:17:41.394 align:middle line:84%
I often say, who came up with
this concept of alarm clock?

00:17:41.394 --> 00:17:43.963 align:middle line:84%
Who thought, okay, the best
way we can start the day is

00:17:43.963 --> 00:17:46.966 align:middle line:84%
in a state of alarm, you
know, adrenalin cortisol alarm,

00:17:46.966 --> 00:17:51.104 align:middle line:84%
the worst way to start our
day and yet most of us,

00:17:51.104 --> 00:17:53.106 align:middle line:90%
so ditch the alarm clock.

00:17:53.106 --> 00:17:56.443 align:middle line:84%
Get a soothing clock, you know,
that likes classical music,

00:17:56.443 --> 00:17:59.312 align:middle line:84%
whatever you like, something
that kind of wakes you up slowly

00:17:59.312 --> 00:18:01.214 align:middle line:84%
or one of those sunshine
alarm clocks.

00:18:01.214 --> 00:18:04.017 align:middle line:84%
You know, it kind of
re-creates the dawn rising

00:18:04.017 --> 00:18:05.118 align:middle line:90%
and stuff like that.

00:18:05.118 --> 00:18:06.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: You don't
want to brutally wake

00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:08.354 align:middle line:90%
up from this lucid dreaming.

00:18:08.354 --> 00:18:10.457 align:middle line:84%
I mean do you have a sense
of the time that there is

00:18:10.457 --> 00:18:12.392 align:middle line:84%
in reality, I mean
in this reality?

00:18:12.392 --> 00:18:14.394 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, so in a
lucid dream time is relative

00:18:14.394 --> 00:18:15.695 align:middle line:90%
to this reality.

00:18:15.695 --> 00:18:17.997 align:middle line:84%
So in a non-lucid dream
time is out the window.

00:18:17.997 --> 00:18:19.399 align:middle line:90%
You know, you can have a dream.

00:18:19.399 --> 00:18:21.634 align:middle line:84%
It seems like hours and it has
lasted 20 minutes or something.

00:18:21.634 --> 00:18:23.970 align:middle line:84%
In a lucid dream time
is relative to this.

00:18:23.970 --> 00:18:25.538 align:middle line:84%
So they've done this
with scientific studies

00:18:25.538 --> 00:18:26.806 align:middle line:90%
where they got people to go

00:18:26.806 --> 00:18:29.109 align:middle line:84%
into lucid dream state and flick
their eyes, saying begin

00:18:29.109 --> 00:18:31.277 align:middle line:84%
and then they estimate
five minutes in time

00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:34.147 align:middle line:84%
and flick their eyes again to
say I think it is five minutes.

00:18:34.147 --> 00:18:36.716 align:middle line:84%
They've shown it's roughly
the same as this state.

00:18:36.716 --> 00:18:39.519 align:middle line:84%
So imagine the conversation that
we've had now in, I don't know,

00:18:39.519 --> 00:18:40.987 align:middle line:90%
ten minutes or something.

00:18:40.987 --> 00:18:43.990 align:middle line:84%
Imagine what you could do in
ten minutes in your psyche.

00:18:43.990 --> 00:18:47.026 align:middle line:84%
Imagine what you could
explore inside your own mind

00:18:47.026 --> 00:18:49.963 align:middle line:84%
within even 30 seconds
let alone ten minutes.

00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:51.764 align:middle line:84%
And a lucid dream, you
could have lucid dreams

00:18:51.764 --> 00:18:54.167 align:middle line:84%
up to 90 minutes in
length which is kind of,

00:18:54.167 --> 00:18:57.036 align:middle line:84%
once you're past kind of, eight,
nine hours in bed you're going

00:18:57.036 --> 00:18:58.972 align:middle line:84%
to have very, very
long dream periods

00:18:58.972 --> 00:19:03.142 align:middle line:84%
and those can be lucid
in the whole period.

00:19:03.142 --> 00:19:04.677 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: So where
do you start from?

00:19:04.677 --> 00:19:07.380 align:middle line:84%
Does it start from
an intention or?

00:19:07.380 --> 00:19:08.781 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, intention
definitely the most

00:19:08.781 --> 00:19:09.983 align:middle line:90%
important thing.

00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:12.552 align:middle line:84%
For the book I was
interviewing some Lamas and one

00:19:12.552 --> 00:19:14.587 align:middle line:84%
of the Lamas I interviewed
was -- there's the book!

00:19:14.587 --> 00:19:16.789 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Beautiful
book by the way,

00:19:16.789 --> 00:19:20.693 align:middle line:90%
my God, the cover is so great.

00:19:20.693 --> 00:19:22.929 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: I know we shouldn't
judge books by their covers

00:19:22.929 --> 00:19:24.831 align:middle line:84%
but if you've got a really
badass cover I think it does

00:19:24.831 --> 00:19:25.932 align:middle line:90%
help a little.

00:19:25.932 --> 00:19:26.833 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yeah, your
friend did good work.

00:19:26.833 --> 00:19:28.034 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Yeah, he did.

00:19:28.034 --> 00:19:31.104 align:middle line:84%
What were we talking
apart from badass covers?

00:19:31.104 --> 00:19:32.472 align:middle line:90%
Oh Lamas, okay.

00:19:32.472 --> 00:19:33.907 align:middle line:90%
The badass Lama.

00:19:33.907 --> 00:19:35.241 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: The intention.

00:19:35.241 --> 00:19:36.442 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: The intention yes,
the Lama Zangmo

00:19:36.442 --> 00:19:39.612 align:middle line:84%
who is the female Lama who
runs the Buddhist center

00:19:39.612 --> 00:19:43.716 align:middle line:84%
where I live near London Bridge,
I was asking her about the kind

00:19:43.716 --> 00:19:45.285 align:middle line:84%
of most important
aspect of Dream Yoga

00:19:45.285 --> 00:19:47.554 align:middle line:84%
and I thought she was going to
give me some sort of, you know,

00:19:47.554 --> 00:19:49.756 align:middle line:84%
secret Tibetan formula
to the lucid dream state.

00:19:49.756 --> 00:19:52.392 align:middle line:84%
And she thought about it
and she said, Charlie,

00:19:52.392 --> 00:19:54.260 align:middle line:84%
the most important thing
for Dream Yoga, and I said,

00:19:54.260 --> 00:19:55.395 align:middle line:90%
yeah, yeah, what is it?

00:19:55.395 --> 00:19:57.330 align:middle line:84%
And she went you've got
to really want to do it.

00:19:57.330 --> 00:19:59.666 align:middle line:84%
You have to be fired
up and I was like,

00:19:59.666 --> 00:20:01.334 align:middle line:90%
you've got to be fired up?

00:20:01.334 --> 00:20:03.736 align:middle line:84%
You know, I won't find that in
the Tibetan text and she said,

00:20:03.736 --> 00:20:05.638 align:middle line:90%
no, but this is the truth.

00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.674 align:middle line:84%
You know, you've got
to really be fired up.

00:20:07.674 --> 00:20:10.410 align:middle line:84%
If you really believe that
lucid dreams are your birthright

00:20:10.410 --> 00:20:12.845 align:middle line:84%
that you can do it, to remind
yourself that you did it

00:20:12.845 --> 00:20:14.614 align:middle line:84%
as a child, that the
children naturally do it.

00:20:14.614 --> 00:20:16.482 align:middle line:84%
It's not something that we
need to learn how to do it,

00:20:16.482 --> 00:20:18.418 align:middle line:84%
it's something we need
to remember how to do,

00:20:18.418 --> 00:20:20.186 align:middle line:90%
that it is in our capacity.

00:20:20.186 --> 00:20:22.855 align:middle line:84%
You know the capacity of
the mind is that which knows

00:20:22.855 --> 00:20:24.958 align:middle line:84%
so in fact a lucid
dream is not weird.

00:20:24.958 --> 00:20:27.060 align:middle line:84%
Non-lucid dreaming,
perhaps, is weird

00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:30.630 align:middle line:84%
because lucidity is a natural,
spontaneous arising of the mind.

00:20:30.630 --> 00:20:33.032 align:middle line:84%
So to remind yourself of this
be really geered up to do it,

00:20:33.032 --> 00:20:34.667 align:middle line:90%
a really strong intention.

00:20:34.667 --> 00:20:36.302 align:middle line:84%
That's probably the
most powerful technique.

00:20:36.302 --> 00:20:38.037 align:middle line:84%
But then of course
there's all the other stuff

00:20:38.037 --> 00:20:39.973 align:middle line:84%
with dream diaries
and reality checks

00:20:39.973 --> 00:20:42.208 align:middle line:84%
and falling asleep
consciously and self-hypnosis

00:20:42.208 --> 00:20:44.377 align:middle line:90%
and all the techniques.

00:20:44.377 --> 00:20:46.646 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Yeah, yeah,
yeah because once you have

00:20:46.646 --> 00:20:49.749 align:middle line:84%
that intention, I mean great
but then is it a matter

00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:52.518 align:middle line:84%
of also setting one just before
sleeping and saying, hey,

00:20:52.518 --> 00:20:56.055 align:middle line:84%
you know, speaking to you,
yourself inside and saying,

00:20:56.055 --> 00:20:58.257 align:middle line:84%
hey man, you know, I want
to wake up where I want

00:20:58.257 --> 00:20:59.792 align:middle line:90%
to be able to consciously dream.

00:20:59.792 --> 00:21:01.261 align:middle line:90%
I mean this is a whole training.

00:21:01.261 --> 00:21:04.230 align:middle line:84%
It seems so far out
when we start.

00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:05.632 align:middle line:90%
>> Morley: Yeah absolutely.

00:21:05.632 --> 00:21:06.866 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Because we feel we're
not in control of our dreams,

00:21:06.866 --> 00:21:08.635 align:middle line:84%
like it kind of happens and
there's a period of time

00:21:08.635 --> 00:21:11.471 align:middle line:84%
where we dream more than
others but apart from that.

00:21:11.471 --> 00:21:12.805 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, most
people don't even remember

00:21:12.805 --> 00:21:13.539 align:middle line:90%
their dreams.

00:21:13.539 --> 00:21:14.807 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Yeah.

00:21:14.807 --> 00:21:16.109 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: You know, the
majority of people if you talk

00:21:16.109 --> 00:21:17.644 align:middle line:84%
to them they say, you know,
I don't remember my dreams

00:21:17.644 --> 00:21:20.647 align:middle line:84%
or I don't dream and sometimes I
get complacent because I teach

00:21:20.647 --> 00:21:23.116 align:middle line:84%
within kind of Buddhist
circles and spiritual circles

00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:25.351 align:middle line:84%
and I start to just assume
everyone remembers their dreams

00:21:25.351 --> 00:21:26.853 align:middle line:90%
and everyone has a dream life.

00:21:26.853 --> 00:21:30.456 align:middle line:84%
And then when I do more kind
of public talks and I realize,

00:21:30.456 --> 00:21:31.524 align:middle line:90%
you know people don't.

00:21:31.524 --> 00:21:32.692 align:middle line:84%
People just don't
remember their dreams.

00:21:32.692 --> 00:21:35.028 align:middle line:84%
People tell me they
don't dream and I try

00:21:35.028 --> 00:21:37.063 align:middle line:84%
to explain scientifically
everybody dreams four

00:21:37.063 --> 00:21:39.766 align:middle line:84%
or five times a night,
blah, blah, blah.

00:21:39.766 --> 00:21:41.134 align:middle line:90%
But there's a long way to go.

00:21:41.134 --> 00:21:43.369 align:middle line:84%
But the first thing is
recognizing that you dream.

00:21:43.369 --> 00:21:45.138 align:middle line:84%
The second thing is
setting your intention

00:21:45.138 --> 00:21:47.940 align:middle line:84%
to remember your dreams because
unless you remember your dreams

00:21:47.940 --> 00:21:49.809 align:middle line:84%
you're not going to
have lucid dreams

00:21:49.809 --> 00:21:52.745 align:middle line:84%
because a lucid dream
is based on.

00:21:52.745 --> 00:21:54.781 align:middle line:84%
You know, if we take this
from the dream diary thing,

00:21:54.781 --> 00:21:57.150 align:middle line:84%
the more conscious you are of
what you're dreaming about,

00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:58.184 align:middle line:90%
the more likely you are

00:21:58.184 --> 00:21:59.786 align:middle line:84%
to become conscious
within the dream.

00:21:59.786 --> 00:22:01.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Yes.

00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:02.355 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: So the first
thing is to become conscious

00:22:02.355 --> 00:22:04.457 align:middle line:84%
of what you're dreaming about,
so keeping a dream diary,

00:22:04.457 --> 00:22:06.759 align:middle line:84%
setting that intent,
writing down your dreams.

00:22:06.759 --> 00:22:08.861 align:middle line:84%
Then you'll start to get
to know the territory.

00:22:08.861 --> 00:22:10.563 align:middle line:84%
You know, get to know the
territory of the dream.

00:22:10.563 --> 00:22:12.065 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I always dream
about being in a forest.

00:22:12.065 --> 00:22:13.399 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I always dream
on the planet Mars.

00:22:13.399 --> 00:22:14.600 align:middle line:84%
I always dream about
this or that.

00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:16.269 align:middle line:84%
So the next time you're
on the planet Mars

00:22:16.269 --> 00:22:18.304 align:middle line:84%
in the dream I think oh,
I always dream about this.

00:22:18.304 --> 00:22:20.239 align:middle line:90%
Oh, and you become lucid.

00:22:20.239 --> 00:22:22.208 align:middle line:84%
You know, you get to know
the territory so well

00:22:22.208 --> 00:22:24.343 align:middle line:84%
that you'll know the
territory when you're in it.

00:22:24.343 --> 00:22:27.447 align:middle line:84%
Now I could blindfold you and
take you into a bakery, right,

00:22:27.447 --> 00:22:29.449 align:middle line:84%
can't see the bakery but
I bet you could tell me,

00:22:29.449 --> 00:22:30.483 align:middle line:90%
oh, I'm in a bakery.

00:22:30.483 --> 00:22:31.384 align:middle line:90%
You know the sounds.

00:22:31.384 --> 00:22:32.585 align:middle line:90%
You know the smell.

00:22:32.585 --> 00:22:34.187 align:middle line:90%
You can hear the conversations.

00:22:34.187 --> 00:22:37.957 align:middle line:84%
So too with the dream, we need
to get to know the dream so well

00:22:37.957 --> 00:22:41.094 align:middle line:84%
that even if we're
blindfolded, as in non-lucidity,

00:22:41.094 --> 00:22:43.029 align:middle line:84%
we'll be able to tell
when we're in the dream

00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:45.565 align:middle line:84%
and that revelation is the
blindfold being revealed

00:22:45.565 --> 00:22:49.569 align:middle line:84%
and that experience from the
dream as real as this reality.

00:22:49.569 --> 00:22:51.704 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: Sometimes we remember
more in the morning, no?

00:22:51.704 --> 00:22:55.541 align:middle line:84%
And is there a time during the
night or the day, the night

00:22:55.541 --> 00:22:58.611 align:middle line:84%
or whenever we're asleep
that we can better remember?

00:22:58.611 --> 00:22:59.846 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah, on
the retreats I run.

00:22:59.846 --> 00:23:01.481 align:middle line:84%
I run these like
four-day retreats

00:23:01.481 --> 00:23:04.083 align:middle line:84%
and on the retreats
we'll be sleeping

00:23:04.083 --> 00:23:07.987 align:middle line:84%
from about 10:30 till 3:00 in
the morning and then from 3,

00:23:07.987 --> 00:23:10.323 align:middle line:84%
then I start waking everyone up
every 90 minutes.

00:23:10.323 --> 00:23:12.725 align:middle line:84%
So the first like, the first
three cycles, basically, first

00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:15.294 align:middle line:84%
four and a half hours you're on
your bed and then I come

00:23:15.294 --> 00:23:17.296 align:middle line:84%
around with a gong and everyone
wishes they'd never met me.

00:23:17.296 --> 00:23:18.731 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: There's
the alarm clock.

00:23:18.731 --> 00:23:20.633 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: And then if they
like they can then move

00:23:20.633 --> 00:23:23.703 align:middle line:84%
into the shrine room and we have
a sacred sleeping area set up.

00:23:23.703 --> 00:23:25.204 align:middle line:84%
It's like another bed
but very just thin

00:23:25.204 --> 00:23:27.006 align:middle line:90%
blanket and stuff like that.

00:23:27.006 --> 00:23:29.742 align:middle line:84%
So you make some divide
between the sleep of rest

00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:31.711 align:middle line:84%
which is the first
three or four cycles

00:23:31.711 --> 00:23:33.646 align:middle line:84%
where you're getting your delta
wave, your deep sleep

00:23:33.646 --> 00:23:35.248 align:middle line:84%
and the next few cycles
which is when you're doing

00:23:35.248 --> 00:23:36.482 align:middle line:90%
mainly dreaming.

00:23:36.482 --> 00:23:38.818 align:middle line:84%
And in that case I'm waking
everyone in 90 minutes

00:23:38.818 --> 00:23:40.553 align:middle line:84%
so you're writing down
your dreams at 3 o'clock,

00:23:40.553 --> 00:23:43.389 align:middle line:84%
then again at 4:30, then
again at 6, you know.

00:23:43.389 --> 00:23:45.358 align:middle line:84%
So there are periods all through
the night you can remember

00:23:45.358 --> 00:23:46.726 align:middle line:90%
your dreams.

00:23:46.726 --> 00:23:49.162 align:middle line:84%
Most people however find in
the early morning it's easier

00:23:49.162 --> 00:23:50.329 align:middle line:90%
