00:33:00.245 --> 00:33:02.915 align:middle line:84%
of lucid dreaming within
Tibetan Buddhism is preparation

00:33:02.915 --> 00:33:04.483 align:middle line:90%
for the death and dying state.

00:33:04.483 --> 00:33:08.020 align:middle line:84%
So you know straight off the
bat this isn't about working

00:33:08.020 --> 00:33:09.588 align:middle line:84%
with kind of self-hypnotic
ideas.

00:33:09.588 --> 00:33:10.889 align:middle line:90%
This isn't about exploration.

00:33:10.889 --> 00:33:12.524 align:middle line:84%
This definitely isn't about
sex and skateboarding.

00:33:12.524 --> 00:33:14.193 align:middle line:84%
This is about going
and then preparing

00:33:14.193 --> 00:33:16.128 align:middle line:84%
for the big sleep
at the end of life.

00:33:16.128 --> 00:33:19.398 align:middle line:84%
Because it is said that once you
die you don't just get reborn.

00:33:19.398 --> 00:33:21.333 align:middle line:84%
You aren't reincarnated
straight away.

00:33:21.333 --> 00:33:22.968 align:middle line:90%
You enter the bardo state.

00:33:22.968 --> 00:33:25.838 align:middle line:84%
Bardo is a Sanskrit word
that means place in between.

00:33:25.838 --> 00:33:27.873 align:middle line:90%
In fact this life is a bardo,

00:33:27.873 --> 00:33:30.576 align:middle line:84%
its existence is a
succession of bardos.

00:33:30.576 --> 00:33:34.446 align:middle line:84%
But in this case the after-death
bardo is said to be a dreamlike,

00:33:34.446 --> 00:33:36.882 align:middle line:84%
hallucinatory experience
that we enter

00:33:36.882 --> 00:33:39.051 align:middle line:84%
into once the mind
stream has separated

00:33:39.051 --> 00:33:41.653 align:middle line:84%
from the gross corporeal
body at the point of death.

00:33:41.653 --> 00:33:44.456 align:middle line:84%
So basically you die, your mind
stream separates from this thing

00:33:44.456 --> 00:33:48.026 align:middle line:84%
because this is dying and
enters into a bardo state

00:33:48.026 --> 00:33:49.361 align:middle line:84%
which is a little
bit like a dream.

00:33:49.361 --> 00:33:51.764 align:middle line:84%
It's not a dream but it's
a little bit like it.

00:33:51.764 --> 00:33:54.466 align:middle line:84%
So it's said that if you can
train yourself to become lucid

00:33:54.466 --> 00:33:56.201 align:middle line:84%
in the dream you're
training yourself

00:33:56.201 --> 00:33:57.936 align:middle line:90%
to become lucid in the bardo.

00:33:57.936 --> 00:33:59.138 align:middle line:90%
So rather than go aha

00:33:59.138 --> 00:34:01.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm dreaming, you might
go aha I'm dead.

00:34:01.840 --> 00:34:03.575 align:middle line:84%
Now why the hell would you
want to say, aha I'm dead?

00:34:03.575 --> 00:34:05.177 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like a
nightmare right?

00:34:05.177 --> 00:34:08.213 align:middle line:84%
But, apparently if you had that
realization of aha I'm dead,

00:34:08.213 --> 00:34:11.583 align:middle line:84%
full realization in the bardo
this contains the potential

00:34:11.583 --> 00:34:13.919 align:middle line:84%
for full spiritual
enlightenment, you know,

00:34:13.919 --> 00:34:17.890 align:middle line:84%
top deck stuff and highest,
highest potential is

00:34:17.890 --> 00:34:19.591 align:middle line:84%
if you could become
lucid in the bardo.

00:34:19.591 --> 00:34:21.559 align:middle line:84%
And every time you
train in lucid dreaming,

00:34:21.559 --> 00:34:22.928 align:middle line:90%
whether you know it or not,

00:34:22.928 --> 00:34:25.030 align:middle line:84%
you are training
your mind's capacity

00:34:25.030 --> 00:34:26.532 align:middle line:90%
to recognize the bardo state.

00:34:26.532 --> 00:34:28.901 align:middle line:84%
And that's a great
practice to do,

00:34:28.901 --> 00:34:32.271 align:middle line:84%
that means every time we do
this practice we're training

00:34:32.271 --> 00:34:34.472 align:middle line:90%
for that moment of death

00:34:34.472 --> 00:34:38.844 align:middle line:84%
and every lucid dream we have
brings the fear of death,

00:34:38.844 --> 00:34:41.313 align:middle line:84%
actually not further
actually, closer towards us

00:34:41.313 --> 00:34:42.481 align:middle line:90%
but in a fearless way.

00:34:42.481 --> 00:34:45.584 align:middle line:84%
We go towards that
fear and we say,

00:34:45.584 --> 00:34:48.153 align:middle line:84%
yeah death is coming
and I'm ready for it.

00:34:48.153 --> 00:34:50.622 align:middle line:84%
But you know, I could die
tomorrow so let's make sure

00:34:50.622 --> 00:34:53.325 align:middle line:84%
that tonight I practice for my
death so that I'm ready for it,

00:34:53.325 --> 00:34:56.428 align:middle line:84%
so that we can die with
a little bit less fear,

00:34:56.428 --> 00:34:59.364 align:middle line:84%
a little bit more mindfulness,
a little bit more awareness

00:34:59.364 --> 00:35:01.900 align:middle line:84%
to allow us to enter into that
state as we do in our dreams

00:35:01.900 --> 00:35:04.670 align:middle line:84%
with compassion and
with lucidity.

00:35:04.670 --> 00:35:09.041 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: What is the purpose
of Buddhism or how do Buddhists,

00:35:09.041 --> 00:35:11.643 align:middle line:84%
