make it even more succinct.

00:35:54.052 --> 00:35:55.754 align:middle line:84%
And Buddha said,
train your mind.

00:35:55.754 --> 00:35:58.824 align:middle line:84%
You know Buddhism is a
series of practices engaging

00:35:58.824 --> 00:36:01.527 align:middle line:84%
in mind training, to train
the mind to be stronger

00:36:01.527 --> 00:36:05.497 align:middle line:84%
and more flexible and more
liable to recognize illusion

00:36:05.497 --> 00:36:08.600 align:middle line:84%
because the recognition of
illusion, the illusion of self

00:36:08.600 --> 00:36:12.104 align:middle line:84%
and other, the illusion of
separateness is the foundation

00:36:12.104 --> 00:36:16.341 align:middle line:84%
of the mistake, you know,
of believing that I'm better

00:36:16.341 --> 00:36:18.443 align:middle line:84%
than you, you know, this
egocentric awareness

00:36:18.443 --> 00:36:22.281 align:middle line:84%
that we step into is based on
a fundamental misunderstanding

00:36:22.281 --> 00:36:25.217 align:middle line:84%
that you're different from
me and in fact, you're not.

00:36:25.217 --> 00:36:30.789 align:middle line:84%
You're an expiration of
oneness is a natural arising

00:36:30.789 --> 00:36:33.992 align:middle line:84%
or a natural endpoint
of mind training.

00:36:33.992 --> 00:36:36.395 align:middle line:84%
When we train the mind to a
point where it's so flexible

00:36:36.395 --> 00:36:39.698 align:middle line:84%
and so strong and so
