00:50:37.034 --> 00:50:39.804 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: So in the lucid
dream hands do strange things.

00:50:39.804 --> 00:50:41.639 align:middle line:84%
So one of the ways, if you
think you're in a lucid dream

00:50:41.639 --> 00:50:44.475 align:middle line:84%
but you can't tell for
sure you look at your hand

00:50:44.475 --> 00:50:45.810 align:middle line:90%
and you look away again.

00:50:45.810 --> 00:50:47.412 align:middle line:84%
You look back or you look at
your, flip it over a couple

00:50:47.412 --> 00:50:51.282 align:middle line:84%
of times and very often your
hand will blur or glitch

00:50:51.282 --> 00:50:52.750 align:middle line:84%
or you'll get like an
extra finger coming out

00:50:52.750 --> 00:50:53.818 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:50:53.818 --> 00:50:55.553 align:middle line:84%
It's to do with a kind
of a brain process

00:50:55.553 --> 00:50:58.790 align:middle line:84%
that finds it difficult to
replicate detail patterns.

00:50:58.790 --> 00:51:00.792 align:middle line:84%
So this is the easiest
detail pattern to look

00:51:00.792 --> 00:51:02.093 align:middle line:90%
at that's attached to your body.

00:51:02.093 --> 00:51:03.761 align:middle line:84%
So you look at the detailed
pattern, flip it over,

00:51:03.761 --> 00:51:06.531 align:middle line:84%
flip it back and often the
brain because it's not working

00:51:06.531 --> 00:51:10.635 align:middle line:84%
to full capacity will
create an imperfect pattern

00:51:10.635 --> 00:51:12.670 align:middle line:84%
and then you can
tell you're dreaming.

00:51:12.670 --> 00:51:15.139 align:middle line:84%
>> Lilou: So it's kind
of like in "Inception",

00:51:15.139 --> 00:51:17.475 align:middle line:84%
