that movie, didn't you?

00:51:17.475 --> 00:51:18.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Morley: Yeah,
yeah so when it came

00:51:18.910 --> 00:51:20.912 align:middle line:84%
out I did a series
of talks on it.

00:51:20.912 --> 00:51:23.614 align:middle line:84%
Of course in "Inception" he has
so many lucid dreams he wakes

00:51:23.614 --> 00:51:26.017 align:middle line:84%
up in the morning, thinks
am I dreaming or not?

00:51:26.017 --> 00:51:28.386 align:middle line:84%
So he spins his little
spinning top and he thinks well

00:51:28.386 --> 00:51:31.222 align:middle line:84%
if it falls over that means I'm
awake because there's gravity

00:51:31.222 --> 00:51:34.459 align:middle line:84%
and if it keeps on spinning
then that means that I'm still

00:51:34.459 --> 00:51:35.960 align:middle line:90%
in the lucid dream state.

00:51:35.960 --> 00:51:38.529 align:middle line:84%
So this is like our totem, we
want to tell if we're dreaming

00:51:38.529 --> 00:51:39.831 align:middle line:90%
or not, we look at our hand

00:51:39.831 --> 00:51:42.266 align:middle line:84%
and if the hand stays stable
then there's a good chance

00:51:42.266 --> 00:51:43.634 align:middle line:90%
that we are in fact awake.

00:51:43.634 --> 00:51:47.338 align:middle line:84%
Of course the cool thing about
"Inception", spoiler alert,

00:51:47.338 --> 00:51:50.842 align:middle line:84%
